<h1>🇵🇷 Puerto Rico — Complete Country Guide</h1>

<h2>🌏 Introduction</h2>

<p>
<strong>Puerto Rico</strong>, officially known as the <strong>Commonwealth of Puerto Rico</strong>, is an island territory located in the <strong>Caribbean Sea</strong> and is an unincorporated territory of the United States.
</p>

<p>
It is famous for its tropical beaches, rainforests, Spanish colonial architecture, and vibrant Latin culture.
</p>

<p>
Puerto Rico blends Caribbean traditions with American influence, making it a unique cultural destination.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>📍 Capital City</h2>

<p>
The capital city of Puerto Rico is <strong>San Juan</strong>.
</p>

<p>
San Juan is the largest city and the main political, economic, and tourism hub of the island.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>🏙 Major Cities</h2>

<ul>
<li>San Juan — Capital</li>
<li>Ponce</li>
<li>Bayamón</li>
<li>Carolina</li>
<li>Caguas</li>
<li>Arecibo</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>👥 Population</h2>

<p>
Puerto Rico has a population of approximately <strong>3.2 million</strong> people.
</p>

<p>
Most residents are of mixed Spanish, African, and Indigenous Taíno heritage.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>🗣 Languages</h2>

<p>
The official languages are <strong>Spanish</strong> and <strong>English</strong>.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>💰 Currency</h2>

<p>
The official currency is the <strong>United States Dollar (USD)</strong>.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>🌍 Geography</h2>

<p>
Puerto Rico is an island located in the northeastern Caribbean, east of the Dominican Republic.
</p>

<ul>
<li>El Yunque Rainforest</li>
<li>Cordillera Central mountains</li>
<li>Mona Island</li>
<li>Vieques Island</li>
<li>Culebra Island</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>🌦 Climate</h2>

<p>
Puerto Rico has a <strong>tropical climate</strong> with warm temperatures year-round and a hurricane season from June to November.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>🏛 History</h2>

<p>
Puerto Rico was a Spanish colony for over 400 years before becoming a U.S. territory in 1898 after the Spanish-American War.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>📈 Economy</h2>

<p>
The economy is based on manufacturing, tourism, pharmaceuticals, and services.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>🏭 Industries</h2>

<ul>
<li>Pharmaceuticals</li>
<li>Tourism</li>
<li>Manufacturing</li>
<li>Finance</li>
<li>Agriculture</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>⛏ Natural Resources</h2>

<p>
Puerto Rico has fertile land, beaches, forests, and limited mineral resources.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>🏙 Urban Development</h2>

<p>
San Juan and surrounding areas are highly developed with modern infrastructure, tourism facilities, and ports.
</p>

<hr>
<hr>

<h2>🏛 Government</h2>

<p>
Puerto Rico is a <strong>self-governing territory of the United States</strong> with its own constitution and local government.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>🌍 Foreign Relations</h2>

<p>
Foreign relations are handled by the United States, but Puerto Rico maintains cultural and economic connections with Caribbean nations.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>🙏 Religion</h2>

<p>
The majority religion is <strong>Christianity</strong>, mainly Roman Catholicism and Protestant denominations.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>🦜 Wildlife</h2>

<p>
Puerto Rico has rich tropical biodiversity, especially in forests and coastal regions.
</p>

<ul>
<li>Puerto Rican Parrot</li>
<li>Coquí frogs</li>
<li>Sea turtles</li>
<li>Manatees</li>
<li>Iguanas</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>🏞 Environment & Climate Challenges</h2>

<p>
Puerto Rico faces hurricanes, flooding, deforestation, and coastal erosion challenges.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>🚗 Transportation</h2>

<p>
Transportation includes highways, buses, taxis, and ferries between islands.
</p>

<ul>
<li>Road networks</li>
<li>Public buses (AMA)</li>
<li>Taxis and ride-sharing</li>
<li>Ferries</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>✈ Major Airports</h2>

<ul>
<li>Luis Muñoz Marín International Airport (San Juan)</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>🚆 Railways</h2>

<p>
Puerto Rico has no major passenger railway system, only limited metro (Tren Urbano in San Juan).
</p>

<hr>

<h2>🚢 Ports</h2>

<ul>
<li>Port of San Juan</li>
<li>Port of Ponce</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>🎓 Education</h2>

<p>
Puerto Rico has several universities including the University of Puerto Rico system.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>🏥 Healthcare</h2>

<p>
Healthcare is modern and follows the U.S. system with public and private facilities.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>✈ Tourism</h2>

<p>
Puerto Rico is a major Caribbean tourist destination known for beaches and historic sites.
</p>

<ul>
<li>Old San Juan</li>
<li>El Yunque National Forest</li>
<li>Vieques Bioluminescent Bay</li>
<li>Castillo San Felipe del Morro</li>
<li>Culebra beaches</li>
</ul>

